‡§ù‡§£‡§ù‡§£‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§ö‡§ø‡§ï‡§® ‡§•‡§æ‡§≥‡•Ä ‡§®‡§µ‡•Ä‡§® ‡§ó‡•Ö‡§∏‡§∂‡•á‡§ó‡§°‡•Ä ‡§µ‡§∞ Chicken Curry¬†Faber Hob Gas Stove wid 3Stove Burner @FaberSpaIndia

Shop Now: https://shorturl.at/BkaSM

Nothing beats a homemade Chicken Curry slowly cooked to juicy perfection on my Faber Hob Glass Stove 3 Burner! The automatic gas stove ensures even cooking, while the magic lift burners make cleaning super easy. The precise flame adjustments make cooking easy and give the chicken a tenderness that later melts in the mouth. Plus, with FFD safety, I can focus on flavours without worries. Cooking just got smarter and smoother! 

@FaberSpaIndia

For chicken marination & Chicken stock -
 ‚Ä¢ Chicken 1/2 kg 
 ‚Ä¢ Turmeric 1 tsp 
 ‚Ä¢ Salt 1 tsp
 ‚Ä¢ Oil 1 tbsp 
 ‚Ä¢ Onion 1 med (finely chopped) 
 ‚Ä¢ Water 
For Watan / Gravy 
 ‚Ä¢ Dry coconut 1/2 cup grated 
 ‚Ä¢ Onion sliced 3 med onion sliced 
 ‚Ä¢ Tomatoes 1 med sliced 
 ‚Ä¢ Garlic 15-20 cloves 
 ‚Ä¢ Ginger 2 inch 
 ‚Ä¢ Fresh coriander 1/4 cup 
 ‚Ä¢ Red chilly powder 1 tsp 
 ‚Ä¢ Kanda lahsun masala 2-3 tsp 

 ‚Ä¢ For Curry 
 ‚Ä¢ Oil 4 tbsp 
 ‚Ä¢ water 
 ‚Ä¢ Cooked chicken 
 ‚Ä¢ Salt 
 ‚Ä¢ Chopped fresh coriander 

To Marinate chicken & chicken stock -
 ‚Ä¢ Take washed chicken into a bowl, to this add turmeric & salt  mix well & keep it for marination for 30 minutes
 ‚Ä¢ After marination, heat up some oil into a vessel, add chopped onions and saute 
 ‚Ä¢ then add marinated chicken, saute on high flame for couple of minutes
 ‚Ä¢ then cover with a lid, pour some water onto the lid and cook on low flame for 3-4 mins
 ‚Ä¢ then add water from the plate to the chicken, add more hot water and cook chicken on low flame
For Making watan -
 ‚Ä¢ Dry roast dry coconut and take it out
 ‚Ä¢ then add some oil, add sliced onions and roast the onions then add tomatoes and saute tomatoes along with the onions
 ‚Ä¢ allow the roasted ingredients to cool down
 ‚Ä¢ then take roasted coconut, onions & tomatoes to the grinding jar, to this add garlic, ginger, fresh coriander , red chilly pw & kanda Lasun, masla add some water and grind to fine paste
To make curry -
 ‚Ä¢ Heat up some oil, add ready watan / gravy and saute until watan release the oil 
 ‚Ä¢ then add cooked chicken, salt & water if required and cook for 5-6 minutes
 ‚Ä¢ At last add chopped fresh coriander and our delicious chicken curry is ready
 ‚Ä¢ Enjoy with jowar roti or rice

title: CHICKEN CURRY FOR BACHELORS | SIMPLE CHICKEN CURRY FOR BEGINNERS | CHICKEN GRAVY
description:
Chicken Curry For Bachelors | Simple Chicken Curry For Beginners | Chicken Gravy | Chicken Curry | Bachelor Chicken Curry | Chicken Masala Powder Curry | Easy Chicken Curry | Chicken Masala

***********************
For Vegetarian Recipes follow our sister channel @SpiceSwad 
***********************

Ingredients for Simple Chicken Curry:

- Chicken- 1 kg
- Onion, rough chopped- 4 medium
- Ginger, crushed- 2 tsp
- Garlic, crushed- 2 tsp
- Tomatoes, roughly chopped- 3 medium
- Green chillies, thick chopped- 3 nos.

- Turmeric powder- 1/2 tsp
- Red Chilli Powder- 1.5 tsp
- Readymade Chicken Masala- 1 tbsp (store bought)

- Salt- 1.5 tsp
- Refined Oil- 4-5 tbsp 

Preparation:

- Clean & wash the chicken pieces and keep it to drain.
- Roughly chop the onions, tomatoes and green chillies.
- Peel and crush the ginger and garlic cloves.

Process:

- Heat oil in a pan or kadai and add the chopped onions.
- Fry on high heat for 10 mins till brown in colour.
- Add the crushed ginger and garlic and fry on medium heat for 2 mins.
- Add the chopped tomatoes and green chillies and fry on medium heat for 2 mins.
- Add the turmeric powder and mix & fry on medium heat for around 3 mins till tomatoes are soft.
- Now add the chicken pieces and fry on high heat for 2-3 mins till the chicken pieces are browned.
- Add the readymade chicken masala, red Chilli powder and salt, mix and bhunno on high heat for 5 mins. Continue to fry on medium heat for another 5 mins.
- Now add 200 ml water and cook on low heat for around 20 mins till the chicken pieces are tender and oil separates.

title: Dhaba Style Chicken Masalaüòç #shorts #chicken #viral
Simple chicken curry üçõ
description:
Simple Chicken Curry

Ingredients:
- 2 red onions, thinly sliced
- 5 cloves garlic, finely chopped
- 1kg (35 oz) chicken thighs, skinless and diced
- 4 tomatoes, diced
- 2 tbsp oil
- 2 tsp garam masala
- 2 tsp curry powder
- 1 tsp cumin
- 1 tsp chilli powder if you like it spicy
- 400ml (14 oz) water
- salt to taste
- rice, to serve
- optional: yoghurt and coriander for garnish

Method:
1. Heat a large pot over high heat and add the oil. Once the oil is hot, add the chicken with a big pinch of salt. Saut√© over medium-high heat until the chicken is sealed on the outside, then remove the chicken from the pan and set aside.
2. Using the same pan, add a little more oil if needed, and place it back over high heat. Add the onions and cook for 3-4 minutes until they start to brown, then add the garlic and cook for another 1-2 minutes.
3. Next, add the spices (garam masala, curry powder, and cumin) and the diced tomatoes. Stir well, making sure to scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.
4. Pour in the water and bring to a simmer. Cook for 10‚Äì12 minutes until the tomatoes and onions are completely soft.
5. (Optional) For a smooth gravy, blend the sauce at this stage using a hand blender.
6. Add the chicken back to the sauce and continue to cook for 10‚Äì12 minutes until the chicken is fully cooked through.
7. Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt if needed.
8. Serve the curry with rice, and optionally garnish with yoghurt and fresh coriander.

title: Best Crispy Corn Recipe !!
description:
RESTAURANT STYLE CRISPY CORN 

Hello Foodies!!!
Today I am sharing with you a restaurant-style crispy corn recipe. This simple crispy corn recipe requires only a few ingredients, so give it a try and enjoy the crispy and tasty crispy corn !!

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢Boil Water
‚Ä¢1/4 tsp Turmeric
‚Ä¢1 cup Sweet Corn
‚Ä¢2 tbsp Corn flour
‚Ä¢2 tbsp Maida
‚Ä¢1 tbsp Water
‚Ä¢Salt & Pepper
‚Ä¢Oil for deep frying
‚Ä¢2 tbsp Oil
‚Ä¢2 tbsp Onion choppings
‚Ä¢1 tbsp Garlic gratings
‚Ä¢1 Green Chili Choppings
‚Ä¢1/4 tsp White pepper powder
‚Ä¢1/8 tsp Black pepper
‚Ä¢1 tsp Chili flakes
‚Ä¢1/4 tsp Aromat/Ajinomoto
‚Ä¢2 tbsp Spring Onion choppings

title: BBQ style ‚ÄòCrispy corn üåΩ‚Äô #shorts #crispycorn #bbqnation #crispycornfry #cornrecipe #cornsnacks
Crispy Fried Corn ‡•§ ‡§ö‡§ü‡§™‡§ü‡•á ‡§ï‡•Å‡§∞‡§ï‡•Å‡§∞‡•á ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡•Ä‡§ü ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® ‡•§ Spicy Crispy Corn
description:
Crispy Corn Kernels, Crispy Spicy Buttery Corn, ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§™‡•Ä ‡§ö‡§ü‡§™‡§ü‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡•Ä‡§ü ‡§ï‡•ã‡§∞‡•ç‡§®, crispy corn chaat recipe
#CrispyFriedCorn #SweetCorn #SpicyCrispyCorn

Ingredients for Crispy Sweet corn
Sweet corn (‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡•Ä‡§ü ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® ) - 1 cup 
Corn flour (‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® ‡§´‡•ç‡§≤‡§æ‡§∞ ) - 2 tbsp 
Salt (‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï ) - 1/2 tsp 
Red chili powder (‡§≤‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞ ) - 1/2 tsp 
Oil (‡§§‡•á‡§≤ ) - for frying 

For Serving 
Green chili (‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö ) - 2 (finely chopped) 
Green coriander (‡§π‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ß‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ) - 1 to 2 tbsp (finely chopped) 
Lemon (‡§®‡•Ä‡§Ç‡§¨‡•Ç ) - 1/2 or 1 tsp lemon juice 

How to make Crispy Sweet corn : 
1. Take a vessel, fill with 2 cups water.Turn on flame. Let the water boil.Put the sweet corn to boil in water for 5 to 6 minutes.
2. Take it out from water.Put it in the sieve. Keep in bowl. 
3. Add cornflour, red chili powder, salt. Mix all ingredients well, till sweet corn is coated. If it is still powdery, then add 1/2 or 1 tsp water.
4. Heat oil in wok. Once rightly hot, put the sweetcorn to fry.Spread it with a laddle. Keep the flame low medium and Roast sweetcorn for 3 minutes. Gradually increase flame. Keep check on it. Cover the wok. 
5. To take out the sweetcorn, Take an extra sieve, take out sweet corn, hold it on the edge of the wok. Meanwhile reduce flame, keep fried sweet corns in a plate. It takes 5 minutes to fry sweetcorn once.
6. For garnishing, take finely chopped green chili, green coriander, Add black pepper or dry mango powder. Add a little lemon juice to it. Mix all ingredients well.

Serving : 
7. Crispy sweet corn are ready to be served. You can serve it as an appetizer at a party or just munch on it.

title: Crispy Corn | Chatpata Corn Recipe | Easy Snack Recipe | Corn Recipes
description:
Crispy Corn | Chatpata Corn Recipe | Easy Snack Recipe | Corn Recipes

#crispycorn #snacks #cornrecipes #snacksrecipes #crispycornrecipe #homecooking

We all love corn in general. Crispy corn is one way to enjoy corn, it is spicy, tangy and so good that it will make you want more. You just can't stop with one small cup. Do try this recipe and let me know how it turned out for you. 

Prep time: 10 minutes
Cook time: 20 minutes 
Number of servings: 4-5 persons

Ingredients

Corn Kernel - 2 cups
Corn flour - 3 Tbsp
Rice flour - 1 Tbsp
Chili powder - 1 Tsp
Chaat masala - 1/2 Tsp
Spring Onion whites
Chopped Capsicum 
Spring Onion greens
Lemon juice
Pepper
Salt to taste 
Water 

Sweet Corn Fried Rice recipe - https://goo.gl/XeVPpj
Corn Palak Tikki recipe - https://goo.gl/AAtu32

Method 

1. Take the corn kernels in a bowl and add cornflour, rice flour, salt and pepper and toss it 
2. Sprinkle some water and mix the corn kernels so that the batter coats the corn kernels evenly 
3. Heat some oil for deep frying and start deep frying the corn kernels till they turn golden brown in color 
4. Now take the fried kernels in a bowl and add spring onion whites, capsicums, spring onion greens, chili powder, chat masala, and lemon juice and mix this well 
5. Your Crispy Corn in Indian Style is ready to be served immediately 

#crispycorn #cornrecipe #vegstarter

You can buy our book and classes on http://www.21frames.in/shop

ENJOY OUR RECIPES

title: Salt & Pepper Crispy Corn Recipe | Restaurant Style | ‡§π‡•ã‡§ü‡§≤ ‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡§æ ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§™‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® | Chef Sanjyot Keer
description:
Full written recipe for Salt & Pepper Crispy Corn

Prep time: 15-20 minutes 
Cooking time: 10-15 minutes 
Serves: 3-4 people

Ingredients:
Coating & frying
SWEET CORN | ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡•Ä‡§ü ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® 2 CUPS
SALT | ‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï TO TASTE
BLACK PEPPER POWDER | ‡§ï‡§æ‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞ A LARGE PINCH
GINGER GARLIC PASTE | ‡§Ö‡§¶‡§∞‡§ï ‡§≤‡§π‡§∏‡•Å‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡•á‡§∏‡•ç‡§ü 1 TSP
REFINED FLOUR | ‡§Æ‡•à‡§¶‡§æ 2 TBSP 
CORN FLOUR | ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® ‡§´‡•ç‡§≤‡•ã‡§∞ 6-8 TBSP
WATER | ‡§™‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä A SPLASH
Tossing
OIL | ‡§§‡•á‡§≤ 1 TBSP
ONION | ‡§™‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú‡§º 1 TBSP (CHOPPED)
GINGER | ‡§Ö‡§¶‡§∞‡§ï 1 TSP (CHOPPED)
GARLIC | ‡§≤‡§π‡§∏‡•Å‡§® 1 TBSP (CHOPPED)
YELLOW BELL PEPPER | ‡§™‡•Ä‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§∂‡§ø‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö 1 TBSP (CHOPPED)
CAPSICUM | ‡§∂‡§ø‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö 1 TBSP (CHOPPED)
RED BELL PEPPER | ‡§≤‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§∂‡§ø‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö 1 TBSP (CHOPPED)
GREEN CHILLI | ‡§π‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö 2-3 NOS. (SLIT)
VINEGAR | ‡§∏‡§ø‡§∞‡§ï‡§æ ¬º TSP
SALT | ‡§®‡§Æ‡§ï TO TASTE
BLACK PEPPER | ‡§ï‡§æ‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö A LARGE PINCH (FRESHLY CRUSHED)
SUGAR | ‡§∂‡§ï‡•ç‡§ï‡§∞ A PINCH
SPRING ONION GREENS | ‡§π‡§∞‡•á ‡§™‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú‡§º ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡§§‡•ç‡§§‡•á A HANDFUL (CHOPPED)
Method:
Add the sweet corn kernels in boiling water &  boil for 3-4 minutes, then transfer the boiled corn to a big size mixing bowl & allow it to cool down for couple of minutes, make sure you spread them evenly so that the excess steam escapes.
Further add salt, ginger garlic paste, black pepper powder & mix well.
Then add the entire amount of maida & 3 TBSP of cornflour, mix with light hands so the corn coats well.
Then add a splash of water & recoat the corns with only cornflour, add 1-2 TBSP of corn flour at a time & repeat the process of coating flour 3-4 times so it gets coated evenly.
Let the corn kernels rest for a while after coating.
Set oil in a wok for deep frying, before frying sift the coated corn using a sieve or a spider to remove excess flour, carefully add the coated corns in batches in moderately hot (165¬∞ C) oil on medium heat, cover the vessel with a lid for the first minute just as a precaution if any kernel pops, then remove the lid & fry over medium flame until crisp
Once fried remove in a strainer so to get rid of excess oil. Keep this crispy corn aside until you toss further ingredients.
Set a wok over high heat, add oil & let it get hot. 
Further add onion, ginger, garlic, all three bellpeppers & green chilli, stir well & saute over high flame for a minute. 
Then add the crispy corn & the remaining ingredients, toss well over high flame for a minute again. 
Your delicious salt & pepper crispy corn is ready.

title: 5 Tips to make Crispy Corn I Crispy Corn Recipe I ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡•ç‡§ü‡•ã‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç‡§ü ‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§™‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® I Pankaj Bhadouria
description:
5 Tips to make Crispy Corn I Crispy Corn Recipe I ‡§∞‡•á‡§∏‡•ç‡§ü‡•ã‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç‡§ü ‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§™‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•â‡§∞‡•ç‡§® I Pankaj Bhadouria

Crispy Corn is one of our favourite starters when we go to a restaurant. But when we try to make Crispy Corn at home, it does not turn out to be crispy at all and turns soggy.
I am sharing with you 5 tips as to how you can ensure that your crispy corn stay crispy even after an hour! If you follow these tips, your Crispy Corn will not turn soggy at all and remain crispy all the time. 
Crispy Corn is a quick starter that can be made in a jiffy and can be ahead of time. Sor Crispy Corn can be a perfect party starter too!

Thank you for watching! üí´ And don‚Äôt forget to subscribe here:
https://goo.gl/mQwVjN
****************************************************************************
Recipe : 
Crispy Corn
Preparation Time: 15 minutes
Cooking Time: 15 minutes
Serves: 3-4

Ingredients:
2 cups frozen corn
¬Ω cup corn flour
¬Ω cup flour
1 tbsp garlic paste
Salt
Pepper
2 tbsp Schezwan paste
2 tbsp Ginger, finely chopped 
2 tbsp Garlic, finely chopped 
2 tbsp Ketchup
1 Capsicum, finely chopped
1 tsp Kashmiri Red Chili Powder 
1 Onion, finely chopped
Oil to fry

Method:
In a large pan, bring to boil 1 litre water with 1 tsp salt. Boil the corn kernels for at least 5 minutes. Drain the corn. 
Place the corn in a large bowl. Add 1 tbsp garlic paste and mix well. Add 2 tbsp flour, 2 tbsp corn flour and toss. Repeat till all the flour and corn flour is used. Sift to remove any loose flour.
Fry in medium hot oil in 2 batches till crisp. Remove on an absorbent paper.
Rest for 2 minutes and refry till golden in colour. 
Heat 1 tbsp oil in a pan. Add the chopped onion, ginger & garlic. Saut√© till golden. Add the chopped green chilies, capsicum and mix. Add the schezwan paste, ketchup, Kashmiri red chili powder, salt & pepper to taste and mix. Add the corn and toss well. Serve hot.

Aloo Paratha is a bread dish originating from the Indian subcontinent. It is a breakfast dish that originated in the Punjab region. The recipe is one of the most popular breakfast dishes throughout the western, central, and northern regions of India as well as the eastern regions of Pakistan. And nothing is better than having it during winter.

Indian Aloo Paratha ‚Äì whole wheat flatbread stuffed with a spicy potato filling. This paratha is best enjoyed with yogurt, pickle, and butter.

ALOO PARATHA RECIPE 

Preparation Time: 15 minutes
Cooking Time: 20 minutes
Serves: 4 
Course: Breakfast 
Cuisine: North Indian

Ingredients
For the Dough 
2 cups whole wheat flour 
1 tsp salt 
2 tbsp gram flour 
¬Ω tsp carom seeds (ajwain)
2 tbsp ghee 
Water as required
2 tsp oil 

For the Filling
2 large potatoes, boiled and grated
1 inch ginger, grated 
2-3 green chillies, finely chopped
1 tbsp fresh coriander leaves
Salt to taste 
¬Ω tsp coriander powder 
1 tsp chilli powder 
¬Ω tsp cumin powder
1/2 tsp fennel seeds 
1 tsp garam masala 
¬º tsp amchur powder 
Ghee for roasting
Butter cubes for garnish
Yogurt to serve
Pickle to serve

Process

For the dough 
‚Ä¢ Add whole wheat flour, gram flour and ghee to a bowl. Mix well and form a crumb like mixture. 
‚Ä¢ Add water as required and knead a soft dough. Cover with a muslin cloth and set aside for 20 minutes or till in use. 
‚Ä¢ Add oil to the dough and knead a little till its absorbed.

For the filling 
‚Ä¢ Add boiled potatoes, onion, green chilli, fresh coriander, salt, coriander powder, chilli powder, cumin powder, garam masala, fennel seeds and amchur powder. Mix well 
‚Ä¢ Divide the prepared dough into equal portions, and form small lemon sized balls. 
‚Ä¢ Roll them into flat disc with a rolling pin and add the prepared stuffing in the centre. 
‚Ä¢ Roll into a potli, remove the excess dough and roll back into a disc. 
‚Ä¢ Heat a tawa, add the prepared paratha and roast on both sides for 30 seconds each, flip over and brush with ghee, flip over and roast till brown spots appear. 
‚Ä¢ Garnish with cubes of butter and serve hot with yogurt and pickle.

description:
Aloo Paratha Recipe - Potato Stuffed Paratha #shorts 

‚ú® Aloo Paratha ‚ú®

Aloo Paratha is an Indian breakfast flatbread made with whole wheat flour, potatoes, spices & herbs. These flavourful paratha‚Äôs are topped with white butter and served with cold yogurt or tea. In in this video I will show you how to make stuffed aloo paratha at home 

#alooparatha #paratharecipe #parathabananekatarika #alookaparatharecipe #indianfood 

Tag All Aloo Lovers üíú

Ingredients 
3 medium boiled potatoes 
1 medium onion 
1 tbsp red chilli powder 
1 tsp coriander powder 
¬Ω tsp dry mango powder 
1 tsp garam masala 
Cilantro 
Salt 
2 tbsp oil 
1 tsp cumin seeds 
1 cup whole wheat flour 
1 tsp ghee 
¬Ω cup water 
Salt to taste 

Method
‚ûä In a bowl add atta (whole wheat flour), salt and ghee.
‚ûãAdd water little by little and start mixing the dough.
‚ûå Knead to form a smooth and soft dough. The dough should be soft, if it isn‚Äôt add little more water
‚ûçYou can also use the dough hook attachment of your stand mixer to knead the dough. 
‚ûéCover and let the dough rest for 15-20 minutes. Divide the dough into equal portions
‚ûè To make the filling, add boiled potatoes in a bowl and mash it 
‚ûê Add chopped green chili, cumin, kashmiri red chilli powder, amchur(dried mango powder), garam masala, salt & cilantro 
‚ûë Mix until everything is well combined stuffing for the paratha is now ready. 
.
.

‚ë´Press with a spatula and cook the paratha until both sides have golden brown spots

veg momos recipe | momos ki recipe | momos banane ki recipe with detailed photo and video recipe. simple and healthy snack recipe inherited from the traditional nepali cuisine. basically, it is plain flour based dumplings steamed with cabbage, carrot and spring onion stuffing. it has become a popular street food in india and is typically served with a red coloured spicy and watery momos chutney.

description:
Veg momos¬†recipe is one of the most requested among Indian-Chinese food recipes.¬†Veg Momos¬†are tantalizing, the traditional food of Tibet. Veg momos¬†or dim sum are steamed dumplings stuffed with a lightly spiced vegetable filling. A popular Tibetan recipe and also a popular North Indian street food. The steamy hot momos are enjoyed the most during chilly winters. 
----------------------------------------------------------------------

title: Chicken Biryani #shorts #chickenbiryani #chickenrecipes
description:
#shortsviral #chickenbiryani #chickendumbiryani 


Please Check the detailed video below

Kachche Gosht ki Hyderabadi Chicken Dum Biryani | Easy Chicken Dum Biryani Recipe
https://youtu.be/9qeRo3juXFk

Simple Chicken Biryani For Beginners | Super Easy Chicken Biryani Recipe For Bachelors
https://youtu.be/U3nU88bKouo

Ingredients:


Cooking Oil - 1 cup
Sliced Onion - 3 medium sized
Garlic Cloves - 10 to 12
Ginger - 2 inches
Green Chilies - 4 to 5
Water - 2 tbsp
Chicken - 1 kg
Star Anise - 1
Green Cardamom - 4
Mace - 1/2 piece
Black Cardamom - 1
Cinnamon Stick - 2 inches
Cloves - 5
Black Pepper - 1/2 tsp
Biryani Masala Powder  - 2 tbsp
Yogurt - 200 grams
Coriander Seeds Powder - 1 tbsp
Cumin Seeds Powder - 1 tsp
Red Chili Powder - 1 tbsp
Turmeric Powder - 1 tsp
Lemon Juice - 2 tsp
Salt - 1 tbsp
Mint Leaves - 1/2 cup
Coriander Leaves - 1/2 cup

Mix all the above given ingredients and marinate the chicken for minimum 2 hours

For Rice
Basmati Rice - 1 kg
Water - 3 to 4 liters
Green Cardamom - 4
Bay Leaf - 1
Cinnamon Stick - 2 inches
Salt - 1 tbsp
Clarified Butter - 1 tbsp
Lemon Juice - 2 tsp
Boil Rice With Given ingredients cook upto 70 percent drain the water and spread over chicken add color as per your choice , fried onion , Ghee _ 2tbsp ,Add Half cup of water to develop steam so that the chicken cook s nicely  Cover the lid cook for 5 minutes on high flame and then  for 50 minutes on low flame.

title: Chicken Biryani | ULTIMATE Chicken Biryani recipe
description:
INGREDIENTS 

Rice - 600 gm wash and soak for 30 min

BIRYANI RICE - 

Water
Bay leaf - 2 nos.
Cardamom - 2 nos.
Clove - 3 nos.
Cinnamon - 1"
Coriander leaves - a little bit chopped
Ghee - 2 tsp
Lime juice - 2 tsp
Salt - 2 tbsp ( water should be salty)

BARISTA 

Onion - 5 nos. 
Thinly sliced and deep fried 


BIRYANI MASALA

Fennel seeds - 1/2 tsp
Cumin seeds - 1/2 tsp
Coriander seeds - 1 tbsp
Black pepper - 1 tsp
Javitri and Jaifal - a small piece 
Clove - 4 nos.
Green Cardamom - 4 nos.
Cinnamon stick - 1"
Bay leaf - 2 nos.

CHICKEN MARINATION

Chicken - 750 gm 
Ginger garlic paste - 2 tbsp
Salt to taste
Red chili powder - 2 tsp
Turmeric powder - 1 tsp
Kashmiri Chilli powder - 1 tbsp
Biryani masala - 1 tbsp
Chicken masala - 2 tsp
Desi Ghee - 1 tbsp
Coriander and mint leaves chopped
Curd - 3 tbsp
Lime juice - 1 whole lime
Fried Onion ( Birista)
****Marinate for atleast an hour****

TO COOK THE CHICKEN 

Ghee - 1 tbsp 
Mustard Oil - 2 tsp

title: dalfry|Dal fry|dal recipe|quick&simple|everyday|fry dal|home made|Full of protein|vegetable&simple|f
description:
: RESTURANT STYEL DAL FRY :- 
1. Toor/ Tur Dal - 1 cup
2. Masoor Dal - 1/2 cup
3. Moong Dal (yellwo) - 1/2 cup
 Wash and Soak the dal for 30mins
In a cooker add the soaked dal, Water, turmeric powder and salt

Water - 2-3 cups depending upon the dal
Turmeric powder- 1-2tsp
Salt- as per taste

Pressure cook with 2 low and 3 medium whistle 
Once done let it cool.

FOR TEH TADKA :-
1. Oil -3-4 tbsp
2. Jeera - 3tbsp
3. Hing - 2tbsp
4. Kashmiri red chilli - 1/2
5. Garlic - 3-4tbsp
6. Green Chilli - 3-4
7. Ginger - 1tbsp
8. Onion- 2-3
9. Tomato - 1-2
10. Ghee- 1tbsp
11. Salt
12. Turmeric powder- 1tbsp
13. Corriender powder- 2-3tbsp
14. Red Chilli powder - 2tbsp
15. Garam Masala - 2tbsp
16. Amchur powder- 1-2tbsp
17. Corriender leaves- 3-4tbsp
18. Kasuri Meethi - 1tbsp
19. Butter/ Ghee - 2-3tbsp

RECIPE :-

1.  Wash and soak (30mins) toor dal, Mong dal and masoor dal.
2. In a cooker add the soaked dal, Turmeric powder, salt and water.
3. Pressure cook it with 2- low and 3- high whistle.
4. In a kadai add Oil, Jeera, hing, dry kashmirir red chilly, garlic, ginger, green chilli and onion. 
5. Saute till golden brown, once done add Tomato. 
6. Next add ghee and let it saute about 5-6 mins on a low flame. 
7. Add Salt, Turmeric powder, red chilli powder, Corriender powder, Garam Masala, Amchur powder and saute well. 
8. Add the boiled dal, lots and lots of corriender leaves and Kasuri Meethi.
9. Top it with 2tbsp of butter or Ghee. 

SERVEING;-
1. Serve this hot with Jeera Rice. 
2. You can replace garam masala with sabji Masala.

And your resturant style of "Dal Fry" is read :-)

title: Dal Fry Restaurant Style | Lunch Recipes | Dal Recipe
description:
Dal Fry Restaurant Style | Lunch Recipes | Dal Recipe
#DalFry #DalRecipe #DaalFry

This is a classic Dal Fry recipe and super simple and easy to make. It is also a healthy recipe that you can make at anytime of the day. It tastes best with jeera rice or pulao. 

Prep time: 30 mins 
Cook time: 45 mins 
Number of servings: 4-5 persons 

Ingredients

Toor Dal - 1/4 Cup
Moong Dal - 1/4 Cup
Masoor Dal - 1/2 Cup
Water
Turmeric Powder - 1/4 Tsp
Ghee - 2 Tsp
Oil - 1 Tsp
Cumin Seeds - 1 Tsp
Red Chili -  2 Nos
Asafoetida Powder - 1/2 Tsp
Curry Leaves 
Onion - 1 No. Chopped
Green Chili - 2 Nos Chopped
Garlic - 1 Tsp Finely Chopped
Ginger - 1 Tsp Finely Chopped
Tomato - 2 Nos Chopped
Turmeric Powder - 1/4 Tsp
Kashmiri Red Chili Powder - 2 Tsp
Salt - 2 Tsp
Kasuri Methi
Water - 1 1/2 Cups
Garam Masala - 1/2 Tsp
Coriander Leaves

Method 
1. Wash and soak all the 3 dals combined together for about 30 minutes 
2. Add a pinch of turmeric powder and pressure cook the dals for about 3 whistles 
3. Open the pressure cooker after the pressure is released from the cooker, mash the dals well and keep it aside 
4. Heat a kadai with some oil and ghee, add cumin seeds, asafoetida, red chilies and curry leaves, roast them 
5. Next, add finely chopped ginger and garlic and green chilies and saute them 
6. Add onions and saute them till they are golden brown in color 
7. Add tomatoes and cook them until they are soft 
8. Add the red chili powder, turmeric powder, kasuri methi and mix them well 
9. Add the cooked dal and mix well 
10. Add enough water and bring it to a boil 
11. Finally add garam masala and coriander leaves.

title: Dal Fry | Sanjeev Kapoor Khazana
description:
Dal fry and jeera rice, dal fry and steamed rice, dal fry and roti - this classic lentil dish teams up well with literally anything! 
DAL FRY

Ingredients

¬Ω cup split pigeon peas (toovar dal), soaked for 30 minutes
¬º cup split Bengal gram (chana dal), soaked for 30 minutes
¬º cup split skinless green gram (dhuli moong dal), soaked for 30 minutes
¬º teaspoon asafoetida (hing)
¬º teaspoon turmeric powder
3 tablespoons butter
1 teaspoon cumin seeds
1 inch ginger, finely chopped
1 tablespoon chopped garlic
2 green chillies, finely chopped
1 medium onion, finely chopped
1 medium tomato, finely chopped
Salt to taste
1 teaspoon red chilli powder
¬Ω teaspoon garam masala powder
1 tablespoon chopped fresh coriander leaves
Juice of ¬Ω lemon 
Fresh coriander sprig for garnishing

Method

1. Heat a pressure cooker. Add drained split pigeon peas, drained split Bengal gram, drained split green gram, asafoetida and turmeric powder and 2¬Ω cups water, mix, cover and cook till 4-5 whistles are released.
2. Heat 1¬Ω tablespoons butter in a deep non-stick pan. Add cumin seeds and saut√© till fragrant. Add ginger and garlic and saut√© for 1 minute.
3. Add green chillies and onion and saut√© till onion turns golden brown. Add tomato and salt and saut√© till tomato turns soft and pulpy.
4. Add chilli powder, garam masala powder, salt and coriander leaves and mix well.
5. Mix the cooked dal mixture. Add it to tomato mixture, mix and cook for 4-5 minutes.
6. Add remaining butter. Switch off heat, add lemon juice and mix well. 
7. Garnish with a coriander sprig and serve hot with green pea pulao.

DHABA STYLE DAL FRY
Preparation Time: 10 minutes
Cooking Time: 20-25 minutes
Serves: 2

Ingredients
For Dal
2 tbsp ghee
¬Ω cup tuvar dal, soaked
3 tbsp moong dal, soaked 
1 inch ginger, sliced 
Salt to taste
¬º tsp turmeric powder
1 tsp red chilli powder
1 green chilli
1 ¬Ω cups water

For Tempering
1 tbsp ghee 
1 tbsp oil 
¬Ω tsp cumin seeds
1 inch ginger, finely chopped 
¬Ω tbsp garlic, finely chopped 
1 medium onion, finely chopped
1 tsp red chilli powder 
¬º tsp turmeric powder
Salt to taste 

For 2nd Tempering
2 tbsp ghee
2 tbsp oil 
3-4 garlic cloves, sliced 
2-3 whole dry kashmiri red chillies
A pinch of asafoetida
¬Ω tsp kashmiri red chilli powder
Coriander leaves, for garnish

Process:-
‚óè Heat ghee in a pressure cooker, add tuvar dal and moong dal to the pressure cooker
and roast for 2-3 minutes.
‚óè Add in ginger, salt, turmeric powder, red chilli powder, salt and green chilli. Mix well.
‚óè Add water, cover and allow to cook for 3 whistles.
‚óè Meanwhile, heat ghee in a pan, add cumin seeds, ginger and garlic, saute till
fragrant.

‚óè Add onions and saute till translucent. Add chilli powder, turmeric powder and salt,
mix well. Cook for 2-3 minutes, till the rawness of the spices is gone.
‚óè Add the boiled dal to this tempering and allow to cook for simmer for 3-4 minutes
‚óè Meanwhile, prepare the second tempering.
‚óè Heat ghee in a pan, add some water. Add garlic cloves, whole dry kashmiri red
chillies, asafoetida, kashmiri red chilli powder and mix well.
‚óè Cook till it splutters.
‚óè Pour the prepared dal into a serving dish, garnish with coriander leaves.
‚óè Pour the prepared tempering and serve hot.

transcript:
Hello Friends, My Name is Shalu. Welcome back to my channel, Shaluzlovebook Hello Friends, My Name is Shalu. Welcome back to my channel, Shaluzlovebook Today I am going to teach you, dhaba style dal Recipe You can also call it Dal Fry or Dal Tadka When ever we visit a Dhaba/Restaurant we order this Dal Fry/Tadka and think as "how it was made" So we will learn today how to make it at home itself. To make it we need.. Tuwar Dal/Arhar Dal/Yellow Split Pigeon Peas... we have to wash it twice.then drain the water So here i have taken almost 1 Cup Yellow Lentils(Dal) I have washed the dal and drained all water. I have soaked the dal for 30 mins. i left it for half an hour and you can see it has enlarged now we're going to boil it in the cooker First we will add the lentils look here, I have added the lentils and now we're going to add 1+1/2 cup of water with this, we will add salt and turmeric 1/2 T.sp Haldi 1/2 T.sp Salt now put the lid on on a high flame, wait for 2 whistles Now See we i have closed the lid of the pressure cooker Take 2 Whistles on high flame and switch off the flame.
let the cooker cool down After cooker has cooled down open the cooker. Check if the Dal has cooked well Yes Friends our dal has cooked well. Now we will prepare a tadka for the dal For Tadka, take a pan/kadhai/Wok and add 2 Tb. spn Ghee(Clarified Butter) I have used Ghee here Ghee and Butter gives a unique flavour to the dal fry/tadka It gives a different taste,aroma to the Dal After the Ghee is Heated add 1 T.sp Cumin Seeds+2 Pinch Asefoetida(heeng) you can increase/decrease the quantity of cumin seeds. Cumin and Heeng gives a very good taste to the Dal Now you can see Friends Cumin Seeds has started Crackling Now we will add 3 Dried Red Chilli Dried Red Chilli Gives a very earthy flavour to the Dal Tadka Now we will add 7-8 cloves of chopped Garlic Apart from this we will add 2 Inch grated Ginger Now mix everything well and saut√© for few seconds IN place of chopped ginger garlic, you can also add the paste I have mixed and saut√©ed all the things well Ginger Garlic should not remain raw Now i am add adding 2 Finely Chopped Onions Cook the Onions on medium flame for 4-5 Mins. or till it turns light golden While cooking the onions, we will also add few spices so that onions and spices cooks together So now i am adding 1/4 T.sp Haldi Powder
1 T.sp Coriander Powder   Mix Everything well We have to continuously stir it and cook it At this point we will also salt so the the onion cooks faster
(i have added 1/2 T.sp Salt) So i have added little salt at this point. Be cautious while adding salt because we have also added salt while boiling the dal. So keep in mind to add the salt in balance :) We will cook the onions while stirring it continuously... So look at this friends.. Here you can see after almost 5 Mins. the Onion is cooked well and has become Golden in colour Now we will add chopped Tomatoes.
I have chopped 2 Big Tomatoes Chopped Cilantro/Coriander Leaves Coriander Leaves gives a very good flavor to the dal Mix everything well Cook the Mixture till the tomatoes become soft and mushy You can also cover and cook while doing so So you can see friends the tomatoes has become soft Add the boiled dal Boiled Dal So we have added the boiled dal and mix everything well. After this we will cook the dal for 4-5 Mins. on Low flame. Cooking the dal on slow flame will increase the flavor So while the dal is boiling we will prepare a tadka for the dal Friends this tadka will make the Dhaba Dal more tasty, Flavourful & Super So lets see what we need to make this tadka Take a tadka pan Add 2-3 T.sp Ghee/Butter   
Let the ghee melt and heat the Ghee has heated up Keep in mind to heat this ghee/Butter/Oil well so that the spices we add into the ghee should crackle right away then only the tadka will be perfect.
Ghee has heated up.. Add 1/2 T.sp Cumin Seeds Add 1/2 T.sp Degi Mirch(Kashmiri Mirch) Kashmiri Mirch is not much spicy but gives a very good red colour to the tadka..also add chopped Coriander Leaves Now our dal is also ready after boiling and tadka is also ready Also again add some chopped Coriander Leaves Take i out the dal in a serving plate/dish Now we will take out the dal in a serving bowl and put the tadka over it We are adding the tadka Our dhada dal fry id ready to be served Please do make it at home and dont forget to share your feedback after making.. Thank u so much for Watching.. Byee.. Shaluzlovebook Pls hit the like button if you like the video Thanks Again Visit Again ! Love u all :)

title: Dhaba Style Dal Fry Recipe
description:
A delicious easy recipe which has now become a forever family favorite!

Ingredients:
2 tbsp cooking oil
2 bay leaves
1 black cardamom
2 cardamom
2 cloves
1 cup chana dal (soaked for 30 minutes)
¬æ tsp red chilli/kashmiri
¬º tsp turmeric
¬º tsp salt
2 cups water
2 tbsp cooking oil
1 tsp cumin
1 tbsp chopped ginger
1 tbsp chopped garlic
3 green chilli (chopped)
1 cup onion (chopped)
1 cup tomato (chopped)
¬Ω tsp salt
¬º tsp turmeric
1 tsp red chilli/kashmiri
¬Ω tsp cumin
1 tsp garam masala
2 tbsp coriander (chopped)
2 tbsp ghee
¬º tsp hing
1¬Ω tsp crushed coriander
3 dry red chilli

Instructions:
1. Drizzle cooking oil in a pressure cooker.
2. Add bay leaves, black cardamom, cardamom and cloves into a pressure cooker and stir.
3. Then, add the chana dal and mix thoroughly.
4. Mix in red chilli, turmeric and salt.
5. Add water and stir well.
6. Place the lid of the pressure cooker on tightly and wait for 3 whistles.
7. Carefully take off the lid and check to see if the dal is cooked.
8. In a separate pan add cooking oil, cumin, ginger and garlic - mix well.
9. Shortly after, add green chillies into your mixture and keep stirring.
10. Add onions and fry until light brown.
11. Add tomatoes and salt whilst continuously mixing.
12. Add turmeric and red chilli.
13. Saute for 4-5 minutes.
14. Add cumin and garam masala.
15. After this, add the dal mixture into the pan and add salt for taste.
16. Add water if needed.
17. Sprinkle coriander and stir.
18. Now place the dal into a dish/container/bowl.
19. In another pan add ghee, hing, crushed coriander and dry red chilli.
20. Drizzle the ghee mixture over the dal.
21. Ready to enjoy!

transcript: today i will show you how to make restaurant style dal fry                                                               firstly , transfer lentil into a pressure cooker   add 2 cups of water, salt and turmeric powder   mix it   cover the lid and bring one pressure on high heat after one whistle, cook it for just 1 min then turn off the flame   heat 2 tbsp of pure ghee into a pan once ghee heats up add cumin seeds, red chili and green chili, saute it for a while     now add fine chopped onions and fry it till it become light pink in color       add ginger garlic paste and all powdered spices, fry it for 2-3 min on medium heat         add grated tomatoes and fry it till water gets dry         meanwhile check the lentil, its cooked nicely , transfer it into the prepared masala transfer cooked lentil into the masala, cook it for 1 min on high heat   after one boil simmer the heat and cook it for 2 min     you can adjust the consistency by adding hot water   garnish it with coriander leaves and green chilies for tadka, heat 2 tbsp of ghee into a tadka pan once ghee heats up add cumin seeds and garlic cloves fry it till it become light pink in color transfer this tadka into the prepared dal

title: One pot dal recipe #recipevideo #dal #onepotmeal #onepot #onepotrecipes #dalrice #dalchawal
description:
This one pot dal recipe is my husband‚Äôs favorite meal ever! 
It‚Äôs quick, super easy, tastes delicious.. I have to make it whenever I‚Äôm pressed for time or just craving something simple and easy. 

Ingredients I used:
- 1/2 cup toor Dal
- 1/4 cup moong dal
- 3/4 tsp mustard seeds
- 3/4 tsp cumin seeds
- pinch of hing
- 3 to 4 green chillies (or as preferred) 
- few curry leaves 
- 1 inch ginger, finely chopped 
- 3 to 4 garlic, smashed 
- 1 onion, diced  
- 1 and 1/2 tomatoes, diced
- 5 cups water 
- salt
- turmeric 
- red chilli powder
- coriander leaves 


#dal #onepot #onepotmeal #onepotdal #onepotmeals #onepotrecipe
transcript: I don't know why people don't make one pot Dal as often and why is it so underated I mean it's so much easier to make taste just the same if not more delicious and you literally need just one pot so less vessels to wash and more energy to save to make this you need to mix together some T and moon Dal wash it a couple of times and soak it in water for 10 minutes directly into your pressure cooker gift TKA with Rye jira Hing green chilies Curry leaves ginger and garlic add in your onions and tomatoes and stir it just for 2 minutes add in some salt turmeric red chili powder and your soaked Dal and pressure cook it for around 2 to three whistles and once it's done garnish it with some coriander leaves and enjoy

title: Kurkuri Bhindi Recipe- Crispy Okra - Bhindi Kurkuri - Spicy Deep fried Bhindi
description:
Kurkuri bhindi is a zingy-spicy crispy deep fried okras served sprinkled with chaat masala.  

Recipe in Hindi - http://nishamadhulika.com/1389-kurkuri-bhindi-recipe.html
Recipe in English - http://indiangoodfood.com/1043-kurkuri-bhindi-recipe.html

Ingredients for Kurkuri Bhindi
Okra ‚Äì 250 grams
Lemon juice ‚Äì 1 tsp
Salt ‚Äì ¬Ω tsp
Red chilly powder ‚Äì ¬º tsp
Gram flour ‚Äì 2 tbsp
Cumin powder ‚Äì ¬Ω tsp
Coriander powder ‚Äì ¬Ω tsp
Turmeric powder ‚Äì ¬º tsp
Gram flour ‚Äì 2 tbsp
Chaat masala ‚Äì ¬Ω tsp
Oil ‚Äì to deep fry

Directions
Getting ready:
1. Rinse the okras well and place them in a sieve to dry.
2. Then chop off the stalk at both ends and divide the okra into two equal haves. Further slice down these chunks in 3 to 4 thin chunks.
3. Remove the seeds. Similarly chop each okra.
Making:
4. In a big mixing bowl take the chopped okras, followed by some salt and lemon juice. Mix well.
5. Then to it add the following ingredients to it ‚Äì red chilly powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, turmeric powder and gram flour. Mix well until the okra is coated nicely.
6. Heat enough oil in a wok or pan and drop the okras to it, as much as possible. Don‚Äôt over flood the oil.
7. Deep fry till they little brown on high flame. After this, reduce the flame to medium-low and continue frying until the chunks get crispy and golden brown in color.
8. Drain out the fried okras on kitchen paper towels to remove excess oil. Similarly fry the rest. Crispy, tangy and lip smacking crispy Bhindi is ready.

Serving:
9. Sprinkle some chaat masala and kurkuri Bhindi is now ready to serve. Have it with your meals or serve them as an appetizer.

KURKURI BHINDI 
Preparation Time: 40 minutes
Cooking Time: 20 minutes
Serves: 2
Course: Main Course
Cuisine: Indian
Ingredients
250 gms lady finger/ bhindi 
salt to taste 
¬Ω tsp red chilli powder 
¬Ω tsp coriander powder
¬Ω tsp cumin powder
1 tbsp dry mango powder
¬Ω tsp chaat masala
¬º cup gram flour
2 tbsp rice flour 
Salt to taste 
1 tsp chaat masala
Oil for frying
Method:-
‚óè Wash the bhindi completely and wipe them dry with paper towel.
‚óè Slice them into one by 4 vertically.
‚óè Sprinkle turmeric powder, chilli powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, garam
masala powder, dry mango powder, chaat masala powder and salt on bhindi one by
one.
‚óè Mix the bhindi well with these masalas. Sprinkle gram flour and rice flour on top of
the bhindi and make sure the bhindi is well coated.
‚óè Marinate the bhindi with this spice mix for an hour.
‚óè Heat sufficient oil in a kadhai to deep-fry the bhindi.
‚óè Fry the bhindi till crisp and golden brown.
‚óè Drain the excess oil on an absorbent paper.
‚óè Sprinkle chaat masala and serve hot.

Note: Kurkuri Bhindi can be served as is or even with a bowl of curd and some rotis on
side.

description:
Kurkuri bhindi recipe. Enjoy the spiced up crunch of Kurkuri Bhindi (Okra). #HappyCookingToYou

Ingredients:
-Bhindi (Okra) 250 gms (washed & pat dry)
-Lal mirch powder (Red chili powder) 1 tsp or to taste
-Garam masala powder 1 tsp
-Haldee powder (Turmeric powder) ¬º tsp
-Namak (Salt) ¬Ω tsp or to taste
-Dhania powder (Coriander powder) ¬Ω tsp
-Baisan (Gram flour) 2 & ¬Ω tbs
-Oil for frying

Directions:
-Wash,pat dry and slice okra vertically into 4 pieces.
-In bowl,add okra,red chili powder,garam masala powder,turmeric powder,salt and coriander powder, mix well and let it rest for 10 minutes.
-Add gram flour,mix well & set aside.
-In pot,heat oil and fry until golden & crispy.

title: Kurkuri Bhindi Recipe | How to Make Crispy Okra-Bhindi Kurkuri | Bhindi Fry By Chef Amrita Raichand
description:
Learn how to make the perfect Crispy Bhindi with this easy Kurkuri Bhindi recipe. Follow along as Chef Amrita Raichand guides you through the step-by-step process of creating this delicious and crunchy snack. Whether you're a fan of okra or just looking for a new recipe to try, this Bhindi Kurkuri recipe is sure to impress your taste buds. Watch now and enjoy the crispy goodness of this flavorful dish!
#kurkuribhindi #recipe #amritaraichand #food 


Kurkure Bhindi- (serves 5-6 people)
Ingredients
Lady finger (Bhindi)- 500gm (washed and dried)
Besan (gram flour )- 1/2 cup
Rice flour ‚Äì 1/4th  cup
Coriander powder - 1 tbsp
Red chilli powder- 1 tbsp
Dry mango powder (Aamchoor) - 1 tbsp
Turmeric powder(haldi) - 1 tsp
Chaat masala - 1 tbsp
Oil- 1 tbsp
Salt - to taste
Oil for deep frying
 
Method:-
1. Wipe the bhindi and ensure they are completely dry before proceeding. Cut them lengthwise into 4 slices each and place them in a large bowl.
2. Add rice flour along with besan, red chili powder, coriander powder, turmeric powder, dry mango powder, oil and a little salt.
3. Mix everything well so that the bhindi is evenly coated with the spices and flours.
4. If the mixture seems too dry, you can sprinkle a few drops of water to help the coating stick to the bhindi.
5. Now heat oil in a deep pan and fry the bhindi in small batches. (Do not overcrowd the pan)
6. Once they are crispy and golden brown, take them out with the help of a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels to remove the excess oil.
7. Sprinkle chaat masala and give it a toss.
Enjoy your crispy and delicious Kurkure Bhindi!

description:
Kurkuri Bhindi Recipe | Kurkuri Bhindi in air fryer | Kurkuri Bhindi Kaise Banate Hain | kurkuri bhindi ki recipe | kurkuri bhindi ki sabji | kurkuri bhindi banane ki recipe | kurkuri bhindi banane ka tarika | kurkuri bhindi kaise banti hai | kurkuri bhindi fry | kurkuri bhindi ki sabji kaise banaen | kurkuri bhindi sabji | ‡§ï‡•Å‡§∞‡§ï‡•Å‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§≠‡§ø‡§Ç‡§°‡•Ä | Crispy Kurkuri Bhindi | Lasuni Bhendi Masala | Bhendi Fry
Non-fried Indian Snack | Easy evening snacks recipe | healthy non-fried snacks recipe | light dinner recipes indian vegetarian | new veg snacks recipes | daily dinner recipes indian | evening snacks recipes healthy | dinner snacks recipe | indian savoury snacks recipe | quick healthy dinner recipes vegetarian indian | Instant breakfast recipes indian 

Air Fryer Store link - https://www.amazon.in/shop/meghnasfoodmagic/list/9U5PV0RW3WGN?ref_=cm_sw_r_cp_ud_aipsflist_aipsfmeghnasfoodmagic_G5P43QJM1EWH7VYW3409_1

One of the most loved Bhindi version but also the most oily; simply because in order to make Bhindi Kurkuri, you need to deep fry it for long.
That‚Äôs why Air Frier comes handy. The oil consumption drops and yet you get crispy Kurkuri Bhindi. 

Secondly, only besan will make Kurkuri Bhindi soft actually; hence have modified the traditional preparation with Rice Flour so that it gets crispy in air fryer. Quick recipe, don‚Äôt miss the tips and tricks.

Ingredients :
300 gm Okra (Bhindi)
3 big spoon Gram Flour (Besan)
2 big spoon Rice Flour (Chawal ka atta)
Salt as per taste 
2 tsp Coriander Powder (Dhaniya Powder)
Pinch of Turmeric Powder (Haldi)
Red Chilli Powder (as per taste)
1 small spoon Dry Mango Powder (Amchur Powder)
1.5 tbs Oil
Chaat Masala (to sprinkle)

Method : 
Take 300 gm Okra, remove its crown and base tip
Slice vertically into 4 pieces
Leave this cut bhindi for an hour 
Further add 3 big spoon Gram Flour
Add 2 big spoon Rice Flour
Add Salt as per taste 
Add 2 tsp Coriander Powder
Add a pinch of Turmeric Powder 
Add Red Chilli Powder (as per taste)
Add 1 small spoon Dry Mango Powder
Add 1.5 tbs Oil and gently mix it for 5 min
Spices and flour must evenly coat the bhindi
Place a parchment paper in the air fryer tray & grease with oil 
Put marinated bhindi in the tray 
Air fry for 15-16 min at 180‚Å∞
Check once after 8 min and shuffle the pieces
Air fry for another 8 min
Remove from the air fryer and leave for 5 min
Take it on a serving plate & sprinkle Chaat Masala 
Enjoy Scrumptious Crunchy Kurkuri Bhindi
.

title: Palak Paneer Thandi ka Mausam Aaya #palakpaneer #youtubeshorts #shorts #trendingshorts
description:
Ingredients:- 

Sugar 1tsp
Salt 1tsp
Baking Soda 1tsp
Spinach Leaves 700g
Mint Leaves 50g
Coriander Leaves 50g
Oil as per Preparation
Cumin Seeds 1tsp
Garlic Chopped 1tbsp
Ginger Chopped ¬Ωtsp
Onions 3 Chopped
Tomatoes 2 Chopped
Green Chilli Chopped
Clarified Butter(Ghee) 1tbsp
Salt As Per Taste
Dry Red Chilli 3
Turmeric Powder ¬Ωtsp
Kashmiri Red Chilli 1tbsp
Cottage Cheese(Paneer) 200g  
Nutmeg
Processed Cheese 1Cube
Fresh Cream 50ml

Process and Preparation :- 

Boil water and add sugar,salt and baking soda, stir it well, and in the boiling water add all the green leaf veggies, Spinach,Mint and Coriander, boil them all for 1 min in the bubbling hot water and immediately remove and add it to cold water, if ice water available then too good, otherwise it's okay to be in normal room temperature water,
Then in a Pan add Oil 2-3tbsp, once oil gets hot add Cumin Seeds and let it crackle for ¬Ωmin then add garlic and ginger chopped, saute it properly, don't burn it, then add the finely chopped onions, once the onions come to transculent and done then add finely chopped tomato and also the green chillies chopped, don't forget to add salt after adding tomatoes, then mix it all and cook to a proper saute roast, then all these sauted veggies and the boiled leaf veggies, grind them all in a mixer to make a puree or a paste, you'll notice that your puree will come glowing green colour, okay all good
Next Step :) in the same pan add ghee then a sprinkle of cumin seed and add turmeric powder, Dry red chilli and Kashmiri red chilli Powder mix them all and then only add the puree or the paste and cook them all for 5-6 min in open, then add paneer and a pinch of grated nutmeg for a beautiful aroma then add the cheese cube, obviously grated, then salt as per needed, cover it and cook for 15 min in low medium flame, that's it, if you have and want to add the fresh cream then add, it will give a rich flavour and creamy texture, otherwise it's okay to have the nutrisious and protien full Dish of Palak Paneer, and also while servind add a slice of butter and sprinkle some roasted chopped garlic it tastes awesome 
So Enjoy the dish and Have a Good Day and Please don't Forget to Share and Subscribe :)

PALAK PANEER
Preparation time: 10 minutes
Cooking time 20 minutes
Serves: 2
Course: Main
Ingredients:
2 bunches, Palak leaves, cleaned, (blanched then in ice cold water )
1 inches ginger, grated
2-3 garlic pods, roughly chopped
2 green chili, chopped
For Palak Paneer
1 tbsp Ghee
1 tbsp oil
¬º tsp cumin seeds
3-4 cloves
1 bay leaf
Pinch of asafoetida
2-3 small onion, chopped
2-3 garlic pods, chopped
1 medium Tomatoes, chopped
1 tsp coriander seeds, roasted and crushed
1/2 tbsp. kasoori methi, roasted and crushed 
¬Ω tsp Turmeric powder
1 tsp Red chilli powder
2-3 leaves of spinach, chopped
2 bunches Spinach, blanched and puree
¬Ω cup hot water
250-300 gm Paneer, cut into cubes
1 tbsp Fresh Cream
Salt as per taste
Garnish
Ginger, julienne
Fresh cream
Process
‚Ä¢ In pot blanch spinach leaves in boiling water for 2-3 minutes. Remove and transfer
immediately into ice cold water.
‚Ä¢ Now into blender add ginger, garlic and make paste then add cooked palak and make
smooth paste
‚Ä¢ For palak paneer heat ghee in pan and add bay leaf, cumin seeds, asafoetida. Stir for a
minute until fragrance goes off.
‚Ä¢ Now add onion and garlic, saute until they turn translucence. Add tomatoes and stir till they
turn soft. Add turmeric, red chilli, kasoori methi, crushed coriander seeds and some coriander powder and mix well. Add some chopped palak leaves.
‚Ä¢ Now add prepared palak puree, hot water, adjust salt and give a nice stir.
‚Ä¢ Transfer paneer cubes, sprinkle garam masala and allow it to cook for another a minute.
‚Ä¢ A finish with fresh cream and fold it into gravy.
‚Ä¢ Garnish with ginger julienne and fresh cream.

title: ‡§™‡§æ‡§≤‡§ï ‡§™‡§®‡•Ä‡§∞ | How to make easy Palak Paneer | Spinach and Cottage Cheese Recipe
description:
Please take a moment to like and subscribe
http://www.youtube.com/c/MadhurasRecipeMarathi?sub_confirmation=1
‚úø‚óï ‚Äø ‚óï‚úø

MadhurasRecipe Marathi Whatsapp Number - 9112934976

Palak Paneer a creamy and rich and is a delight to eat. A dish I fell in love with at a local restaurant and adapted a recipe to closely resemble theirs. You too can try it at home in no time.

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Oil
‚Ä¢ 1 finely chopped medium size Tomato
‚Ä¢ 1 Green chili
‚Ä¢ 3 cups chopped Palak
‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Water
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Oil
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin powder
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Coriander powder
‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp Turmeric powder
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Red chili powder
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Garam masala
‚Ä¢ 2~3 tsp Water
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Cumin seeds
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Garlic paste
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Butter
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Kasuri methi
‚Ä¢ 2 tsp Cream
‚Ä¢ 250 gm Paneer

Method:
‚Ä¢ Heat up oil is a pan. When oil is enough hot, add tomato, green 
  chili and mix well. 
‚Ä¢ Cover and cook on medium heat for about 3-4 minutes until 
  tomato is cooked.
‚Ä¢ Take palak, wash it really good and chop it. Add chopped palak 
  and mix well. 
‚Ä¢ Add a little water and cook for about 3-4 minutes. No need to 
  cover while cooking. 
‚Ä¢ Turn off the gas and let palak cool down. 
‚Ä¢ Transfer the palak into blander pot and make puree. 
‚Ä¢ For making masala paste, in a bowl take cumin powder, coriander 
  powder, turmeric powder, red chili powder and mix well. 
‚Ä¢ Add water and mix well to make paste. Masala paste is ready. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up oil in a pan. Add cumin seeds and let it splutter. 
‚Ä¢ Add garlic paste and mix well and cook for about a minute. 
‚Ä¢ Lower down the heat and add masala paste. 
‚Ä¢ Fry for about 2 minutes until oil is released form masla.  
‚Ä¢ Add palak puree and mix it well with masala. 
‚Ä¢ Add salt and cook palak for about 5-6 minutes to remove raw 
  smell of palak. No need to cover while cooking palak. 
‚Ä¢ Add butter and kasuri methi. 
‚Ä¢ Beat malai and add it. You can add fresh cream too. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and add paneer. 
‚Ä¢ Mix well and cook for just about 4-5 minutes. 
‚Ä¢ Turn off the gas and palak paneer is already. 
‚Ä¢ Palak paneer goes well with naan, kulcha or paratha. 

Tips:
‚Ä¢ Palak is iron rich food. Adding tomato helps for better absorption 
  of iron in body. So while making any palak recipe, add something 
  sour like tamarind, tomato etc. 
‚Ä¢ While adding kasuri methi, crush it with hands and add in any 
  recipe. Kasuri methi gives nice flavour to the dish.
‚Ä¢ If you cook paneer longer, it becomes chewy and loses its 
  softness.  So cook paneer for just about 4-5 minutes.

title: Dhaba Style Palak Paneer Recipeüòç #shorts #paneer #trending
Palak Paneer Recipe | No onion No Garlic Palak Paneer | Navratri Special Recipe | Chef Sanjyot Keer
description:
Full Written Recipe for No onion no garlic palak paneer

Prep time: 15-20 minutes
Cooking time: 202-5 minutes
Serves: 4-5 people

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ Fresh spinach 2 bunch
‚Ä¢ Fresh coriander 2 tbsp
‚Ä¢ Fresh mint 1 tbsp
‚Ä¢ Green chillies 2-3 nos.
‚Ä¢ Ginger 1 inch
‚Ä¢ Paneer 600-700 gm
For gravy
‚Ä¢ Ghee 2 tbsp
‚Ä¢ Cumin seeds 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Whole red chillies 2-3 nos.
‚Ä¢ Bay leaf 2-3 nos.
‚Ä¢ Cinnamon 1 inch
‚Ä¢ Ginger 1 inch (chopped)
‚Ä¢ Green chillies 2-3 nos. (chopped)
‚Ä¢ Asafoetida 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Red chilli powder 1 tbsp
‚Ä¢ Turmeric powder ¬Ω tsp
‚Ä¢ Cumin powder 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Cashew paste 2 tbsp
‚Ä¢ Curd 1/3rd cup
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ Black salt 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Wheat flour 1 tbsp
‚Ä¢ Fresh cream 2-3 tbsp (optional)
‚Ä¢ Garam masala 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Lemon juice 1 tsp
Method:
‚Ä¢ Set water for boiling in a stock pot, blanch the spinach briefly for 10-15 seconds in boiling water and immediately transfer in ice cold water, doing this step helps to retain the bright green colour of the spinach. 
‚Ä¢ Add the blanched spinach in a grinding jar, along with fresh coriander, fresh mint, green chillies & ginger, add water as required and grind to make a fine puree. Keep it aside to be used later.
‚Ä¢ Cut the paneer in your preferred shape and size, set a pan on medium heat, add enough oil for shallow frying the paneer, fry them from all side until golden brown in colour.
‚Ä¢ Further let the fried paneer sit in warm water until used, doing this step helps the paneer to be moist.
‚Ä¢ For making the gravy, set a wok on medium heat, add ghee, jeera, bay leaf, cinnamon, ginger & green chillies, stir once and lower the flame, further add, powdered spices, stir & cook on medium low flame for 1-2 minutes, add little water to avoid the burning of spices.
‚Ä¢ Further add, cashew paste, curd & salt to taste, stir continuously & cook on low flame for a minute.
‚Ä¢ Further increase the flame to medium heat & cook until the ghee separates.
‚Ä¢ Now, add the spinach puree & mix well, add wheat flour to thicken the gravy, stir & cook for 3-4 minutes on medium flame.
‚Ä¢ Now add the shallow fried paneer that‚Äôs been resting in warm water, add some fresh cream, garam masala and lemon juice. Mix gently and cook for a minute.
‚Ä¢ No onion no garlic palak paneer is ready, serve hot with roti of your choice.

Foolproof Rasmalai Recipe By Food Fusion (Ramzan Special Recipe)
description:
This foolproof rasmalai recipe has been tried and tested so that you get it right every time. Just follow the instructions carefully and you will be able to match what you get from your halwai. #HappyCookingToYou #Recipe #Cooking 

Written Recipe: https://bit.ly/359PTzO

Visit Our Website: https://www.foodfusion.com 
Download iOS & Android app: https://www.foodfusion.com/app 
Facebook: https://facebook.com/foodfusionpk 
Instagram: https://instagram.com/foodfusionpk 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/foodfusionpk 
Also Follow @HealthyFoodFusion  & @FoodFusionKids  for healthy food & kids special recipes.


Foolproof Rasmalai
Serves 10-12
Recipe in English:

Ingredients:
-Doodh (Full cream fresh milk) 1 litre
-Zafran (Saffron strands) 1 pinch
-Hari elaichi (Green cardamom) 5-6
-Sugar 6 tbs ot to taste 
-Pista (Pistachios) 1 & ¬Ω tbs 
-Badam (Almonds) 1 & ¬Ω tbs 
-Doodh (Full cream fresh milk) 1 & ¬Ω litre
-Water ¬º Cup
-Lemon juice 3-4 tbs
-Cornflour 2 tsp
-Sugar 1 Cup
-Water 1 litre

Directions:
Prepare Saffron Milk:
-In a pot,add milk and bring it to boil,add saffron strands,green cardamom,sugar,pistachios,almonds and mix well,bring it to boil and cook on low flame until milk is reduced to half (approx. 12-15 minutes) and keep mixing in between.
Prepare Rasmalai Balls:
-In a pot,add milk and bring it to boil then remove from flame and rest for 5-10 minutes to bring down the temperature. 
-In water,add lemon juice and mix well.
-In milk,add lemon juice & water and mix well and rest until milk curdles completely.
-In a bowl,place strainer,muslin cloth and strain the curdle mixture through the strainer to separate whey and rinse with tap water to remove lemon juice completely and squeeze well and hang for 10 minutes.
-In a bowl,add strained cheese and mash well for 10 minutes until its smooth. 
-Add cornflour,mix well and knead the mixture until smooth (approx. 5 minutes).
-Take a mixture (1 tbs) and make smooth rasmalai balls with no cracks then flatten the balls on your palm (makes 13-14).
Prepare Sugar Syrup:
-In a wok,add water,sugar,mix well and cook until sugar is dissolved.
-In sugar syrup,add rasmalai balls & cook for 3 minutes in sugar syrup,cover & cook for 12-15 minutes or until double in size.
-Turn off the flame,add ice cubes and let it rest for 8-10 minutes or until all the ice cubes melt.
-In a serving dish,add prepared saffron milk and rasmalai balls.
-Garnish with pistachios,almonds and saffron.
-Refrigerate for 3-4 hours & serve chilled!

Tips:
-Do not add lemon juice in boiling milk.Wait for few minutes to reduce the milk temperature.
-Knead the cheese curdle for at least 10 minutes to make rasmalai soft.
-Note that after a proper kneading,curdle mixture should not stick to your hands or with spoon.
-After adding lemon juice when curdles begin to form,do not stir the syrup.
-Always prepare sugar syrup in wide wok/pot.

Recipe in Urdu:

Ajza:
-Doodh (Full cream fresh milk) 1 litre
-Zafran (Saffron strands) 1 pinch
-Hari elaichi (Green cardamom) 5-6
-Sugar 6 tbs ot to taste 
-Pista (Pistachios) 1 & ¬Ω tbs 
-Badam (Almonds) 1 & ¬Ω tbs 
-Doodh (Full cream fresh milk) 1 & ¬Ω litre
-Water ¬º Cup
-Lemon juice 3-4 tbs
-Cornflour 2 tsp
-Sugar 1 Cup
-Water 1 litre

Directions:
Prepare Saffron Milk:
-Pot mein doodh dal ker ubal lein,zafran,hari elaichi,cheeni,pista aur badam dal ker ache tarhan mix karein aur ubal anay ka bad halki ancch per doodh adha reh janay tak paka lein (approx. 12-15 minutes) and bech bech mein chamcha chalatay rahein.
Prepare Rasmalai Balls:
-Pot mein doodh dal ker ubal lein aur chulhay sa hata ker 5-10 minutes kliya temperature kum hunay kliya rakh dein.
-Pani mein lemon juice dal ker ache tarhan mix karein.
-Doodh mein lemon juice & pani dal ker mix karein aur milk curdle hunay tak chor dein.
-Bowl mein strainer aur malmal ka kapra rakh dein aur curdle mixture ko strain ker ka whey alag ker lein phir tap water sa ache tarhan dho lein taka lemon juice nikal jaye aur haathon ki madad sa pani ko squeeze ker lein aur 10 minutes kliya hang ker lein.
-Bowl mein strained cheese dal ker 10 minutes ya smooth hunay tak ache tarhan mash ker lein.
-Cornflour dal ker ache tarhan mix karein aur 5 minutes kliya mixture ko smooth hunay tak ghond lein.
-1 tbs mixture lein aur rasmalai balls bana lein (with no cracks) aur haath ki haateli per pheela lein (makes 13-14).
Prepare Sugar Syrup:
-Karhai mein pani aur cheeni dal ker ache tarhan mix karein aur cheeni ghul janay tak paka lein.
-Sheeray mein rasmalai balls dal ker 3 minute kliya paka lein phir dhak ker 12-15 minutes ya size double hunay tak paka lein.
-Chulha bund ker dein aur ice cubes dal ker 8-10 minutes ya ice cubes melt hunay tak chor dein.
-Serving dish mein tayyar saffron milk aur rasmalai balls dal dein.
-Pista,badam aur zafran sa garnish ker lein.
-3-4 hours kliya refrigerate ker lein aur thanda serve karein!

-Pot mein doodh dal ker ubal lein,zafran,hari elaichi,cheeni,pista aur badam dal ker ache tarhan mix karein aur ubal anay ka bad halki ancch per doodh adha reh janay tak paka lein (approx. 12-15 minutes) and bech bech mein chamcha chalatay rahein.
Prepare Rasmalai Balls:
-Pot mein doodh dal ker ubal lein aur chulhay sa hata ker 5-10 minutes kliya temperature kum hunay kliya rakh dein.
-Pani mein lemon juice dal ker ache tarhan mix karein.
-Doodh mein lemon juice & pani dal ker mix karein aur milk curdle hunay tak chor dein.
-Bowl mein strainer aur malmal ka kapra rakh dein aur curdle mixture ko strain ker ka whey alag ker lein phir tap water sa ache tarhan dho lein taka lemon juice nikal jaye aur haathon ki madad sa pani ko squeeze ker lein aur 10 minutes kliya hang ker lein.
-Bowl mein strained cheese dal ker 10 minutes ya smooth hunay tak ache tarhan mash ker lein.
-Cornflour dal ker ache tarhan mix karein aur 5 minutes kliya mixture ko smooth hunay tak ghond lein.
-1 tbs mixture lein aur rasmalai balls bana lein (with no cracks) aur haath ki haateli per pheela lein (makes 13-14).
Prepare Sugar Syrup:
-Karhai mein pani aur cheeni dal ker ache tarhan mix karein aur cheeni ghul janay tak paka lein.
-Sheeray mein rasmalai balls dal ker 3 minute kliya paka lein phir dhak ker 12-15 minutes ya size double hunay tak paka lein.
-Chulha bund ker dein aur ice cubes dal ker 8-10 minutes ya ice cubes melt hunay tak chor dein.
-Serving dish mein tayyar saffron milk aur rasmalai balls dal dein.
-Pista,badam aur zafran sa garnish ker lein.
-3-4 hours kliya refrigerate ker lein aur thanda serve karein!

title: Nolen gurer Rasmalai Recipe#rasmalai #sweet #dessert #nolengur #viralvideo #shorts #recipe #food
Rasmalai | ‡§∞‡§∏‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ‡§à ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§¨‡§∏‡•á ‡§Ü‡§∏‡§æ‡§® ‡§§‡§∞‡•Ä‡§ï‡§æ | All Time Favourite Recipe | Sanjeev Kapoor Khazana
description:
Spongy soft cottage cheese balls dipped in a creamy thickened sweetened milk make for an out of this world delicacy - Rasmalai. Make this heavenly Bengali sweet dish at home now and enjoy.

RASMALAI

Ingredients

2.5 litres full fat milk
2 tbsps white vinegar
2 cups sugar 
A large pinch of saffron strands + for garnish
Blanched, peeled, and slivered pistachios for garnish
Almonds slivers for garnish

Method

1. To make chenna, heat 1.5 litres of milk in a deep pan, bring it to a light boil.
2. Take vinegar in a bowl, add ¬º cup water and mix well. Add this mixture little by little into the milk and cook till the milk curdles. Switch the heat off.
3. Once curdled, add 1 cup water and mix well to reduce the temperature. Strain this mixture through a muslin cloth and a strainer. Collect the chenna in the strainer and gently squeeze out the excess water. Reserve the whey water and transfer the chenna into a large plate and knead till smooth. Divide the mixture into small portions and shape each portion into a ball. Slightly flatten each ball. Immerse them in the reserved whey water.
4. To make the sugar syrup, heat 1¬Ω cups sugar and 4 cups water, mix and cook till sugar melts.
5. Combine the refined flour and ¬º cup whey water in a small bowl.
6. Remove 1 cup sugar syrup in a large bowl and set aside. Add the refined flour mixture in the sugar syrup remaining in the pan, cover and cook till it comes to a boil.
7. Gently slide in the prepared flattened chenna, cover and cook on low heat till it comes to a boil. Add ¬º cup of the whey water and gently mix. Cover again and cook on low heat for 8-10 minutes. Strain the cooked chenna and transfer into the reserved sugar syrup. 
8. Heat remaining milk in a non-stick wide pan, cook on low heat till the milk reduces to half its original quantity while stirring in between.
9. Add saffron and remaining sugar and mix well. Cook till the sugar melts. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes while stirring in between. Allow to cool completely. 
10. Squeeze the cooked chenna to remove excess sugar syrup, soak it into the milk mixture and garnish with blanched pistachios, almond slivers, and saffron strands. Refrigerate till chilled completely. 
11. Serve.

title: Gulab Jamun Recipe | Tips for Soft & Perfect Gulab Jamun | ‡§™‡§∞‡§´‡•á‡§ï‡•ç‡§ü ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§¨ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§®  | Chef Sanjyot Keer
description:
#YFL #SanjyotKeer #GulabJamun

Full written recipe :

Prep time: 5 minutes
Cooking time: 15-20 minutes
Serves: 24 gulab jamuns (depending on the size)

Pro tips:
* Makes sure to cream the mawa & paneer well for softer gulab jamuns.
* The oil should not be too hot while frying.
* The syrup should be warm and not hot while adding the gulab jamuns after frying.

Sugar syrup (chaashni)
Ingredients:
* Cheeni (sugar) 4 cups
* Paani (water) 3 cups
* Gulab Jal (rose water) 1 tbsp
* Choti elaichi (green cardamom) 3-4 pods
Method:
* Take a stock pot or wok, add sugar and water, keep stirring until it dissolves completely, bring to a boil & further add rose water & green cardamom, open the shell of the green cardamom to infuse its flavour, mix well & later switch off the flame. We do not require any sort of one string or two string consistency, it should just be a simple sugar syrup. 
* Keep the sugar syrup aside, no need to cool down, let the temperature drop on its own. Make sure to keep them warm.

Gulab jamun
Ingredients:
* Hariyali mawa 250 gm / 1 cup
* Malai paneer 1/4th cup / 65 gm
* Maida (refined flour) 4 tbsp
* Baking powder 1 tsp
* Oil for frying
Method:
* For making perfect soft gulab jamun we require specifically ‚Äúhariyali mawa‚Äù if it‚Äôs not available you can also use fresh soft mawa, but try to use hariyali mawa for better results.
* Use a big size thal and add the mawa, if the mawa is little tough, use a grater and great to break down or else you could directly start to cream (mathna) the mawa, using the base of your palm. Cream the mawa until its smooth and creamy in texture, there should be no grains in the mawa, you need to do this process for at least 15 minutes or until the entire batch of the mawa is smooth. This process surely may be time consuming but its very important as doing this step will make you a perfect gulab jamun.
Pro tip: cream in small batches for efficient and better results.
* After creaming the mawa, take the malai paneer and grate using a small size hole, you have to cream the paneer as well in the same way as done for mawa, cream it well until its smooth in texture. You can also use chenna if not paneer.
* Once they both are smooth in texture, mix well and add maida in batches, make sure not to add them all at once, the quantity of maida will differ depending on the moisture level in the paneer and mawa, so just add in batches, you need to add & mix well until it forms like a dough and it starts to leave the parath or thal. This recipe, with this quantity won‚Äôt require more than 4 or 5 or 6 tbsp of flour.
* Once it has mixed nicely and formed a dough like texture, add baking powder and incorporate well in the dough.
* Rest the dough for 10-15 minutes & cover with a cloth, by the time you can make the chaashni.
* After making the chaashni, divide the dough in small and equal size balls, make sure to shape them in small shape as they will get bigger in size when they will soak up the chaashni.
* I have a weighing machine so it makes the process easy to keep every ball equal in size, if you have it then please use it or else you can also divide in equal portion roughly, dividing in equal size is necessary because when you‚Äôll fry them, the bigger ones may be little uncooked whereas the smaller ones may burn quickly.
* Shape them in perfect roundels one by one and make sure there should not be any cracks on the gulab jamun, also cover the shaped balls with moist cloth to avoid them from drying, while you‚Äôre shaping few more. By the time your shaping set oil for frying.
* Set a wok filled with oil for frying the gulab jamuns, make sure the oil is not very hot, if you are having a thermometer please use it, the ideal temperature for frying the gulab jamuns should be somewhere 145- 155, if you're not having the thermometer, then drop in one gulab jamun ball to check, if it gets darken too quickly, then cool down the oil little bit. If the ball starts to float in few seconds and the bubbles start to appear then you're good to go.
* Swirl the hot oil with the spatula to make like a whirlpool, make sure to do it carefully and not spilling the hot oil over your hands, stir and add the gulab jamun balls but the spoon not touching them or else they may break, take help if required, fry in batches and do not overcrowd the kadhai.
* Fry them on low flame maintaining the temperature and keep stirring so that they get even colour and cook evenly from the inside as well.
* Once they are nice golden brown, immediately drop them in warm sugar, the temperature of the sugar should not exceed above 50 or the gulab jamun will become too soft and may lose its shape.
* Now, let the gulab jamun rest in the sugar syrup for minimum 4 hours so that they can absorb the syrup nicely. Your perfect gulab jamun is ready to be served, just warm them a little bit before serving to get that perfect soft texture.

* Once they are nice golden brown, immediately drop them in warm sugar, the temperature of the sugar should not exceed above 50 or the gulab jamun will become too soft and may lose its shape.
* Now, let the gulab jamun rest in the sugar syrup for minimum 4 hours so that they can absorb the syrup nicely. Your perfect gulab jamun is ready to be served, just warm them a little bit before serving to get that perfect soft texture.

title: Gits Gulab Jamun | Premix gulab jamun recipe | #shorts #youtubeshorts #foodvlog #gulabjamun
Gulab Jamun quick, easy & authentic Recipe learn how to make at home By Food Fusion
description:
Gulab Jamun Recipe. This time make them at home. Eid is incomplete without Gulab Jamuns. Continue the tradition by making them at home this time. #HappyCookingToYou

Written Recipe: https://bit.ly/2Xtpx9x

Visit Our Website: https://www.foodfusion.com 
Download iOS & Android app: https://www.foodfusion.com/app 
Facebook: https://facebook.com/foodfusionpk 
Instagram: https://instagram.com/foodfusionpk 
Twitter: https://twitter.com/foodfusionpk 
Also Follow @HealthyFoodFusion  & @FoodFusionKids  for healthy food & kids special recipes.

Gulab Jamun 
Recipe in English:

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ Lassa khoya 250 grams
‚Ä¢ Baking soda 1 pinch
‚Ä¢ Salt  1 pinch
‚Ä¢ Flour 1/3 cup
‚Ä¢ Egg ¬Ω 
Syrup: 
‚Ä¢ Water 2 cups 
‚Ä¢ Sugar 1 & ¬Ω cup
‚Ä¢ Kewra water 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Cardamom powder 1/2 tsp
‚Ä¢ Lemon juice 1 tsp

Directions:
To make syrup, in a pan add water and sugar and cook until it becomes a sticky syrup. Now turn off the flame and add kewra water, cardamom powder, lemon juice and mix well.
In a bowl take lassa khoya and crumble it well with your hands. Add flour, baking soda, salt, and egg and mix well to a smooth dough. It needs kneading for at least 6-8 minutes.
Now make small balls of same size. Make sure they are smooth and have no cracks. 
Heat ghee, and add balls and fry gently and stir continuously. Make sure ghee is not very hot otherwise gulab jamun will not cook well from inside or will burn. 
When gulab jamuns becomes golden, add them directly to hot syrup. Make sure syrup is hot (not burning hot). 
Repeat frying process. Add all gulab jamuns in syrup and leave them for 60 minutes
Garnish with pistachios and serve ÔÅä

Recipe in Urdu:

Ajza:
‚Ä¢ lassa khoya 250 grams
‚Ä¢ Baking soda 1 pinch
‚Ä¢ namak  1 pinch
‚Ä¢ Maida 1/3 cup
‚Ä¢ Anda ¬Ω adha
Syrup: 
‚Ä¢ Paani 2 cups 
‚Ä¢ Cheeni 1 & ¬Ω cup
‚Ä¢ Kewra arq 1 tsp
‚Ä¢ Elaichi powder 1/2 tsp
‚Ä¢ lemon juice 1 tsp

Banane ka tareeka:
Ek pan main pani len aur cheeni shamil kar ke pakayen. Jab tak ke garha sheera banjaye. Ab choolhay se utaar len aur kewra arq, elaichi powder and lemon juice shamil kar ke achi tarah mix karlen.
Ek bowl main lassa khoya lekar achi tarah hathon se choora choora kar len. Maida, baking soda , namak, aur anda shamil karke mix Karen. 6-8 minutes tak goondhen taake acha sa paira banjaye. Ab is main se ek hi size ki choti choti golian banalen. Dhiyan rahe ke golian smooth hon aur cracks na hon.
Ab ghee garam kar lain aur ek ek karke golian daalen aur medium aanch par fry Karen. Aanch tez na ho warna gulab jamun jal jayenge ya ander se kache reh jayenge. Jese hi gulab jamun golden hojayen garam sheere main shamil karte jaye. Sheera garam hona chahiye. Ek ghante keliye sheere main hi rehne den aur phir garnish karke serve karen.

GULAB JAMUN RECIPE

Preparation time: 15 minutes
Cooking time: 25 minutes
Serves: 4

Ingredients:
For Gulab jamun
9 tbsp Milk powder , ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§≤‡•ç‡§ï ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞
3 ¬Ω tbsp All purpose flour , ‡§Æ‡•à‡§¶‡§æ
¬Ω tbsp Semolina , ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§ú‡•Ä
3/4 tsp Baking soda , ‡§¨‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ç‡§ó ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞
2 tbsp Curd , ‡§¶‡§π‡•Ä
2 tbsp Milk , ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§ß
1 tsp Ghee, ‡§ò‡•Ä
Ghee for deep frying the gulab jamun, ‡§ò‡•Ä

For Stuffing (per serving)
¬Ω tsp Gulkand, ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§ï‡§Ç‡§¶
1 tsp Pistachios, chopped, ‡§™‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ

For Sugar syrup
250 grams sugar, ‡§ö‡•Ä‡§®‡•Ä
1 cup water, ‡§™‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä
2-3 Cardamom pods, crushed
1 tbsp rose water, ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§¨ ‡§ú‡§≤

For Garnishing
Silver work,‡§ö‡§æ‡§Ç‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§µ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ï (optional)
Rose petals, ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§¨ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡§Ç‡§ñ‡•Å‡§°‡§º‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§Ç
Pistachios, sliced, ‡§™‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ

Process
‚óè In a large bowl, add milk powder, all purpose flour, semolina, baking soda, curd, milk and mix
everything well.
‚óè Make a soft dough, divide the dough into equal portion sizes and roll it like a small ball.
‚óè They must be smooth without cracks or lines. Keep them covered.
‚óè Heat ghee in a kadai, drop a small ball of the dough to check the temperature of the ghee once it's medium hot.
‚óè Start frying the gulab jamun on medium flame make sure the ghee is not too hot or else the
gulab jamun will brown without cooking.
‚óè Fry the balls till light golden. Keep stirring gently so that it cooks from all the sides.
‚óè Add them to the hot syrup. Allow them to rest at least 15-20 minutes.
For Stuffed Gulab Jamun
‚óè Take off one ball and flatten it out with your fingers. Place some stuffing over it and close very
nicely. Roll again and fry it until golden brown.

‚óè Add to the hot sugar syrup and rest for at least 15-20 minutes.
For Sugar syrup

For Gulab jamun
9 tbsp Milk powder , ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§≤‡•ç‡§ï ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞
3 ¬Ω tbsp All purpose flour , ‡§Æ‡•à‡§¶‡§æ
¬Ω tbsp Semolina , ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§ú‡•Ä
3/4 tsp Baking soda , ‡§¨‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ç‡§ó ‡§™‡§æ‡§â‡§°‡§∞
2 tbsp Curd , ‡§¶‡§π‡•Ä
2 tbsp Milk , ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§ß
1 tsp Ghee, ‡§ò‡•Ä
Ghee for deep frying the gulab jamun, ‡§ò‡•Ä
For Stuffing (per serving)
¬Ω tsp Gulkand, ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§ï‡§Ç‡§¶
1 tsp Pistachios, chopped, ‡§™‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ
For Sugar syrup
250 grams sugar, ‡§ö‡•Ä‡§®‡•Ä
1 cup water, ‡§™‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä
2-3 Cardamom pods, crushed
1 tbsp rose water, ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§¨ ‡§ú‡§≤
For Garnishing
Silver work,‡§ö‡§æ‡§Ç‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§µ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ï (optional)

Pistachios, sliced, ‡§™‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ
Process
‚óè In a large bowl, add milk powder, all purpose flour, semolina, baking soda, curd, milk and mix
everything well.
‚óè Make a soft dough, divide the dough into equal portion sizes and roll it like a small ball.
‚óè They must be smooth without cracks or lines. Keep them covered.
‚óè Heat ghee in a kadai, drop a small ball of the dough to check the temperature of the ghee once it's medium hot.
‚óè Start frying the gulab jamun on medium flame make sure the ghee is not too hot or else the
gulab jamun will brown without cooking.
‚óè Fry the balls till light golden. Keep stirring gently so that it cooks from all the sides.
‚óè Add them to the hot syrup. Allow them to rest at least 15-20 minutes.
For Stuffed Gulab Jamun
‚óè Take off one ball and flatten it out with your fingers. Place some stuffing over it and close very
nicely. Roll again and fry it until golden brown.
‚óè Add to the hot sugar syrup and rest for at least 15-20 minutes.
For Sugar syrup
‚óè In a saucepan, add water, sugar, cardamom pods, rose water and dissolve the sugar in water till
it gets thicken on medium flame.
‚óè The sugar syrup should be hot.
For Garnishing
‚óè Serve in a bowl, garnish it with silver work, rose petals and sliced pistachios.

title: Paneer Butter Masala Recipe - Paneer Makhani Recipe
description: Click http://nishamadhulika.com/796-paneer-butter-masala-recipe.html to read Paneer Butter Masala Recipe in Hindi.  Also known as Paneer Makhani Recipe
transcript:
Namaskar
Welcome to nishamadhulika.com Paneer preparations are almost liked by us all. Paneer dish is always prepared for a special occasion or party. They are prepared with numerous unique ways. Today we will make paneer butter masala. Let‚Äôs see what all ingredients are required for making paneer butter masala. Paneer - 250 grams (cut into 1 inch chunks) Paste - 3 tomatoes, 2 green chilly and 1 inch ginger piece Cream - ¬Ω cup Butter - 2 tbsp Green coriander - 2 tbsp (finely chopped) Red chilly powder - ¬º tsp Turmeric powder - ¬º tsp Coriander powder - 1 tsp Dry fenugreek leaves - 1 tsp Salt - ¬æ tsp (as per taste) Garam masala - ¬º tsp Cumin powder - ¬Ω tsp Preheat pan for making paneer butter masala. Now add butter in the pan. When butter melts add cumin powder, coriander powder, turmeric powder and tomato-green chilly paste. Also add red chilly powder. Add dry fenugreek leaves and saut√© until butter starts floating on the surface. Keep stirring after every ¬Ω minute and keep the flame low. Masala is ready, now mix cream into it. Add garam masala and salt. Mix all ingredients really well. Add green coriander leaves and ¬Ω cup water in gravy. Cook until gravy starts boiling. If not stirred constantly the cream may coagulate. Now add paneer chunks into it. Cover the pan and cook Sabzi on low flame for 3-4 minutes. Sabzi is ready; now turn off the gas. Add rest of the butter as well in the gravy. Take out Sabzi in a serving bowl. Garnish with green coriander leaves. This much quantity can be served to 4-5 family members. Serve with chapatti, naan, parantha or rice. Try making this recipe at your home and share your experiences with us. See you again at nishamadhulika.com
